y duration-300" href="/diversity">Diversity &amp; Inclusion</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/sustainability">Sustainability</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/contact">Contact</a></div></nav><button class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e ml-10 toggle-menu absolute top-6 right-6"><img src="/images/misc/menu-closed.svg" alt="Open Menu" class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e"/></button></header><div class="bg-white"><main class="bg-white" style="opacity:0"><article class="px-2 md:px-6 py-10 md:py-12"><header class="flex px-2 md:px-0 md:pb-12 border-b flex-wrap items-center"><div class="md:w-6/12"><picture><img height="1080" width="1920" class="" loading="lazy" src="https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Untitled_design_8_dddd7cd8e9.jpg" alt=""/><sub class="mt-2"></sub></picture></div><div class="md:w-6/12 px-0 md:px-12 py-4 md:py-16 mx-auto max-w-titles small-body"><div class="font-small uppercase mb-4">Jan 15, 2024</div><h2>In The Spotlight: Tristan Xiang</h2><div class="max-w-sm"><div class="rich-text">Vogue China’s Digital Operation Lead Tristan Xiang discusses Lunar New Year, the growth of the brand in the Chinese market and what we can expect in 2024.</div></div><div class="mt-4 md:mt-8 small-body flex flex-wrap"></div></div></header><div class="small-body text-black px-2 md:px-0 py-8 md:py-36 mx-auto news-article-body"><div class="rich-text"><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Tell us a little bit about yourself. How did you find your way to Condé Nast?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I'm from Zhejiang province in China. I graduated with a degree in computer science but yet ended up in the fashion industry, which was a very interesting experience. I started working as a freelancer with Condé Nast and later joined the company. The editor I was working with at that time told me there was a headcount, asking me if I wanted to give it a try, and without hesitation I immediately said, "No matter what, I'm in!" At that time, China's new media landscape was changing rapidly, and as a member of Vogue's new media, I was in the line with the train of the ages.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>How do you describe your job to friends and family?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I always tell my family members that Condé Nast is my second home and they couldn’t agree more.</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I started working at Condé Nast shortly after graduating from college and it's been almost ten years since then. I've been here for almost my entire career, so it's really an irreplaceable sense of belonging. Everyone in my family knows that I work for Vogue (The Fashion Bible). Vogue China observes culture through the lens of fashion, looks at the world today and uses the best photo, video and text production to convey our values to readers. New media is also a very important part of this and I think we are doing something amazing together.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Lunar New Year is approaching soon, what does this holiday mean to you and how do you plan to celebrate?&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">My family's tradition is that the entire extended family stays together for the Lunar New Year. It's a very high-quality time to spend together as a family. So basically, the entire holiday season is filled with family visits, with all the relatives going around and paying New Year's greetings to each other. My parents cook very well, so my stomach will always be full during the New Year.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Another recreational activity is playing mahjong, it's kind of a family tradition and we all participate in. But the moment I look forward to the most is New Year's Eve, my parents will put an auspicious red envelope under my pillow and a letter with their thoughts on the year for me and what they want to say, kinda cliché but it’s romantic and really touching.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Reflecting on this past year, what is a project that you worked on that you are most proud of?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">The projects I worked on in 2023 are Vogue Open Casting, Vogue film, Vogue Craftsmanship Project, Vogue China Fashion Fund and Vogue Forces of Fashion makes its debut in Shanghai, China. It feels like I've done so many projects this year. The project I’m most proud of would be Vogue Open Casting. In 2021, based on Vogue’s essential role in launching and growing talent’s careers, Vogue China holds an annual open casting call – for new faces of all ages and backgrounds. In 2023, for the first time, Vogue open casting went global, more than 1,054,000 "votes" were cast on new faces' "comp card" profiles. Meanwhile, our global call received more than 77,000 entries, which is really inspiring.&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>You have been part of big tentpole events and moments for Vogue China such as Forces of Fashion. Can you tell us about the impact of the event in the market and how it contributes to the growth of Vogue China.</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Nowadays, it's important to capture the attention of the public and the market while maintaining a high level of creativity on a daily basis. The big tentpole events are such highlights through which we connect almost all of our partners - the most influential celebrities, supermodels, photographers, brand clients and readers that Vogue China works with, and it becomes an important program for us.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">It was also an opportunity to showcase the results of our major projects, such as the aforementioned projects, at the big tentpole events, giving the public and the market a more comprehensive view of the “Vogue China Universe.” This is also reflected in the data, as each big tentpole event generates a huge amount of exposure, measured in billions of dollars, with a high level of social media discussion and engagement, and a significant increase in followers.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>You also lead digital channels for the brand. What is something that you are currently working on that will help lead with the progression of those channels?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Everything is changing so fast in China. There are so many digital/social media platforms in China and the environment is changing so fast that we need to keep an eye on the content and operation strategies of different social media platforms. We keep in touch with the official staff of all the platforms for a long time and with high frequency.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">In terms of content, in addition to the content produced by Vogue digital itself, I will also work with other editorial teams at Vogue China to continue to create better IPs that are more engaging for our readers. New media is the most intuitive and timely way to synchronize with readers' feedback, so I will also work with other teams such as the consumer team and the digital team to analyze readers' data and profiles more accurately as support. We also need to focus on what's happening on social media, so my friends love to talk to me about what's going on and they are all surprised about how I know everything. I say, “Because I'm doing new media.”</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>What can we expect to see from the brand in 2024?&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">2024 continues to be a challenging and exciting year. We will continue to do Vogue China’s influential annual projects this year and I believe it will be more mature. At the same time, more projects will arrive, such as Vogue House, which will be launched in 2024. As our Vogue China audience seeks to be more immersed in the brand, we will “come home” to Beijing in the spring 2024 to a standalone house in Beijing with a history to match Vogue’s 131-year legacy.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">This is where our members enter Vogue’s world, brought to life off the page, an ever-evolving curation of culture and offline storytelling through the lens of fashion.Vogue House Beijing is a world-first, always-on offline destination for our engaged community. I'm looking forward to being able to officially see it. In the meantime, I'm looking forward to more changes happening in the digital world!&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Finally, I wish you all a happy new year!</span></p></div></div></article></main></div><div><footer id="footer" class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e px-4 py-4 md:px-6 md:py-6 block bg-near-black"><section class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e border-b border-dark-border pt-12 mb-8 overflow-x-auto"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e snap-mandatory snap-x flex overflow-nav-group"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/about">About</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/brands">Brands</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" hre